{"questionId":"9778","questionHtml":"<p>The Head of Year, Mrs Smith, decides to select a student at random from the year group to&nbsp;read the notices in assembly. There are 80 students in total in the year group. Mrs Smith&nbsp;calculates the probability of picking a male student 8 times in the first 20 assemblies is&nbsp;0.153357 correct to 6 decimal places.</p>\n<p>Find the number of male students in the year group.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>let <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> be the number of male students</p>\n<p>recognize that probability of selecting a male is equal to&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{x}{{80}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>80</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {{\\text{set up equation}}\\,{}^{20}{{\\text{C}}_8}{{\\left( {\\frac{x}{{80}}} \\right)}^8}{{\\left( {\\frac{{80 - x}}{{80}}} \\right)}^{12}} = } \\right)\\,0.153357\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>set up equation</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <msup>\n        <mrow>\n\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>20</mn>\n        </mrow>\n      </msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>C</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>8</mn>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>(</mo>\n              <mrow>\n                <mfrac>\n                  <mi>x</mi>\n                  <mrow>\n                    <mn>80</mn>\n                  </mrow>\n                </mfrac>\n              </mrow>\n              <mo>)</mo>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>8</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>(</mo>\n              <mrow>\n                <mfrac>\n                  <mrow>\n                    <mn>80</mn>\n                    <mo>−</mo>\n                    <mi>x</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                  <mrow>\n                    <mn>80</mn>\n                  </mrow>\n                </mfrac>\n              </mrow>\n              <mo>)</mo>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>12</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>=</mo>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mn>0.153357</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>number of male students = 37&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(M1)A0</strong></em>&nbsp;for 27.</p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9778","referenceCode":"SPM.1.AHL.TZ0.17b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"The Head of Year, Mrs Smith, decides to select a student at random from the year group to read the notices in assembly. There are 80 students in total in the year group. Mrs Smith ","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.8—Binomial distribution"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}